        <fieldset> <legend><h3>What are the roots of the Israel-Palestine conflict?</h3></legend>
        <article class="roots">
            <p>
                People have different opinions on where the problems in the Middle East, especially between Israelis and Palestinians, really began. Some go way back to ancient times, like the Romans. Others start with Jewish people moving to escape persecution in the late 1800s, or the British supporting a Jewish homeland in 1917. But for many, the key moment is the United Nations' decision in 1947 to split the land in Palestine into two parts, one for Jews and one for Arabs, after the Holocaust.
                But why a country decide for another country that what they have to do about their geopolitcal or religious issues without thier permission?
